TITLE: Parsing GEXF Data with Graphology Parser
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to use the GEXF parser to convert GEXF data (string or XML document) into a graphology graph instance with various configuration options.
SOURCE: https://github.com/graphology/graphology/blob/master/docs/standard-library/gexf.md#2025-04-17_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var Graph = require('graphology');

// Node
var gexf = require('graphology-gexf');
// Browser
var gexf = require('graphology-gexf/browser');

// Reading a string
var graph = gexf.parse(Graph, string);

// Reading a dom document
var graph = gexf.parse(Graph, xmlDocument);

// Passing options
var graph = gexf.parse(Graph, string, {addMissingNodes: true});
```

