TITLE: Including Graphology in HTML
DESCRIPTION: HTML script tags to include graphology and its standard library in a web page. It demonstrates how to create a graph object and use the standard library functions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/graphology/graphology/blob/master/README.md#2025-04-17_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: html
CODE:
```
<!-- To use a Graph object -->
<script src="graphology.min.js"></script>
<!-- This exposes a global variable named "graphology" -->
<script>
  const graph = new graphology.Graph();

  const {UndirectedGraph, DirectedGraph} = graphology;
</script>

<!-- To use the standard library -->
<script src="graphology-library.min.js"></script>
<!-- This exposes a global variable named "graphologyLibrary" -->
<script>
  const density = graphologyLibrary.metrics.graph.density(graph);
</script>
```

