TITLE: Using Leiden Community Detection Algorithm
DESCRIPTION: Example usage of the Leiden algorithm implementation showing different ways to detect communities in a graph, including basic usage, direct attribute assignment, custom options, and detailed execution information
SOURCE: https://github.com/graphology/graphology/blob/master/src/communities-leiden/README.md#2025-04-17_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import louvain from 'graphology-communities-leiden';

// To retrieve the partition
const communities = louvain(graph);

// To directly assign communities as a node attribute
louvain.assign(graph);

// If you need to pass custom options
louvain.assign(graph, {
  attributes: {
    weight: 'myCustomWeight',
    community: 'myCustomCommunity'
  }
});

// If you want to return some details about the algorithm's execution
var details = louvain.detailed(graph);
```

