TITLE: Using Unweighted Bidirectional Search in Graphology
DESCRIPTION: Example of using the bidirectional algorithm to find the shortest path between source and target nodes in an unweighted graph.
SOURCE: https://github.com/graphology/graphology/blob/master/docs/standard-library/shortest-path.md#2025-04-17_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import {bidirectional} from 'graphology-shortest-path';
// Alternatively, if you want to load only the relevant code
import {bidirectional} from 'graphology-shortest-path/unweighted';

// Returning the shortest path between source & target
const path = bidirectional(graph, source, target);
```

