TITLE: Using A-star Bidirectional Search for Informed Path Finding
DESCRIPTION: Example of using A* bidirectional algorithm with a heuristic function to efficiently find the shortest path in a weighted graph.
SOURCE: https://github.com/graphology/graphology/blob/master/docs/standard-library/shortest-path.md#2025-04-17_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import {astar} from 'graphology-shortest-path';
// Alternatively, if you want to load only the relevant code
import astar from 'graphology-shortest-path/astar';

// Returning the shortest path between source & target
const path = astar.bidirectional(
  graph,
  source,
  target,
  (_, attr) => attr.importance
  (node, finalTarget) => euclideanDistance(points[node], points[finalTarget])
);
```

