TITLE: Using Louvain Algorithm with Graphology
DESCRIPTION: Example code showing how to use the Louvain algorithm with graphology. Demonstrates retrieving communities as a partition, assigning communities directly to the graph, passing custom options, getting detailed execution information, and ignoring edge weights.
SOURCE: https://github.com/graphology/graphology/blob/master/src/communities-louvain/README.md#2025-04-17_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import louvain from 'graphology-communities-louvain';

// To retrieve the partition
const communities = louvain(graph);

// To directly assign communities as a node attribute
louvain.assign(graph);

// If you need to pass custom options
louvain.assign(graph, {
  resolution: 0.8
});

// If you want to return some details about the algorithm's execution
var details = louvain.detailed(graph);

// If you want to ignore your graph's weights
louvain.assign(graph, {getEdgeWeight: null});
```

