TITLE: Serializing a Graph in Graphology (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates the serialization of an entire graph in Graphology. The serialized format includes graph attributes, options, nodes, and edges.
SOURCE: https://github.com/graphology/graphology/blob/master/docs/serialization.md#2025-04-17_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
graph.mergeEdgeWithKey('T->E', 'Thomas', 'Eric', {type: 'KNOWS'});
graph.setAttribute('name', 'My Graph');
graph.export();
>>> {
  attributes: {
    name: 'My Graph'
  },
  options: {
    allowSelfLoops: true,
    multi: false,
    type: 'mixed'
  },
  nodes: [
    {key: 'Thomas'},
    {key: 'Eric'}
  ],
  edges: [
    {
      key: 'T->E',
      source: 'Thomas',
      target: 'Eric',
      attributes: {type: 'KNOWS'}
    }
  ]
}
```

