TITLE: Detecting Multi-Graph using inferMulti
DESCRIPTION: Function to determine if a graph is truly multi by checking for multiple edges between same nodes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/graphology/graphology/blob/master/src/utils/README.md#2025-04-17_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import {inferMulti} from 'graphology-utils';
// Alternatively, if you want to only load the relevant code:
import inferMulti from 'graphology-utils/infer-multi';

const graph = new MultiGraph();
graph.addEdge(1, 2);

inferMulti(graph);
>>> false

graph.addEdge(1, 2);

inferMulti(graph);
>>> true
```

